MD simulations for microcanonical ensembles (i.e. isolated systems) possess two significant properties: energy conservation and reversibility, which are demonstrated on this page.

Computer simulation techniques, including molecular dynamics, are now practical methods for accelerating discovery of new drugs and new materials. As computational methods develop and computer power increases, computationally screening leading candidates from vast number of combinations will be adopted by more researchers.

Other fields in which molecular dynamics is applied includes mechanical engineering, chemical engineering and fluid dynamics.

 



